	<h3 align="center">How it works?</h3>
	<br>
		<h4>Who Budget Owners?</h4>
	Are you involved with managing budgets for your team? Perhaps your team may have unused budget left over and 
	would like to see certain project progress to production. 
	<br>

	As a budget owners, you can network with other channels and contribute funds to project.
	<br>
	The contributions from you and the other fellow budget owners can help realise innovative ideas at a faster pace.

	<br>
	<h4>Who are FundIT Backers?</h4>
	A 'Backer' is a budget owner, who has committed to contribute funds to a project.
	<h3 align="center">Users</h3>

	<h4>Who are FundIT users?</h4>
	Have you thought of an idea, that will help streamline existing processes. Is there an application, that your peer
	has designed, a prototype for, in which you would like to see developed in near future?

	To realise these innovative ideas, it may be necessary to secure funding to progress them to production. 
	As a user, you can network with other channels and lines of business by:
	<br>
	<ul>
  		<li>Browsing through an archive of projects, that are seeking for funding and support.</li>
  		<li>Endorsing projects posted by your peers to show your support.</li>
  		<li>Asking questions about project you are interested in.</li>
  		<li>Posting your project to secure funding and garner support.</li>
	</ul>
	<br>
	
	<h3 align="center">Benefits.</h3>

	<h4>How does the bank benefit from activity derived from FundIT?</h4>
	<br>
	As a financial institution any bank aims to stream line processes to yeild efficiency gains. The formation of
	the new FundIT community allows employees to share innovative ideas and support progression of projects to production.
	<br>
	On a long term basis, maintaining a single channel such as FundIT is a sustainable solution as it helps
	in funding and implementation processes.
